18/09/2007
PRISTINA, Kosovo, Serbia -- Prime Minister Agim Ceku met on Monday (September 17th) with General John Craddock, NATO's Supreme Allied Commander in Europe, to discuss the current security situation in Kosovo. Craddock assured Ceku that NATO forces are ready to face any challenges that may arise in the course of resolving Kosovo's final status. Ceku, for his part, said all are working to secure stability and co-operation with the international community. (Telegrafi, RTK - 17/09/07)
